713948f-a.title: Manhattan: 58th Street (East) - Lexington Avenue
713948f-a.text:
136 to 116 East 58th Street (foreground, left to right, low houses seen
in full view), at, adjoining and west of the S.W. corner of Lexington Ave.,
as seen across a clearaLnce (extreme foregroundJ at the N.W. corner of the
above mentioned streets, from Finkenberg's Furniture Store, situated at
142-158 East 59th Street, south side, between Lexington and Third Aves.
No. 126-122 appears as a clearance after the demolition of a 5-story house,
which was the home of the New York Genealogical and Biographical Society.
Contiguous to it is seen the 9-story Fullerton House. Also shown is an
extended view of the neighboring area in a southwesterly direction dis-
playing a view of the lower portion of the Ritn Tower (center of picture),
a 41-story apartment hotel, at the N.E. corner of Park Ave. and East 57th
Street.
July 3, 1928.
